div.h2: The Dimension Permutation That Enables Parallel Head Computation

div.p: 3 Parallel Projections Each: nn.Linear(d_model, d_model) Output: [batch, seq, d_model]
Split Heads .view(batch, seq, h, d_k) Last dim becomes h d_k
Heads Unpacked h=8 heads visible in dim 2 Each head: d_k=64 dimensions
Move heads forward .transpose(1, 2) Swap seq_len h
Parallel Computation Ready! Each head: [batch, seq, d_k] Matmul broadcasts over h dimension All 8 heads computed simultaneously
scores = Q @ K^T / d_k weights = softmax(scores) output = weights @ V
Attention Output Same shape as input to attention 8 independent context vectors
Restore sequence dim .transpose(1, 2) Back to [batch, seq, h, d_k]
Concatenate Heads .view(batch, seq, hd_k) Merge last 2 dims
Output Projection nn.Linear(d_model, d_model) Mix information across heads
Final Output Ready for next layer Same shape as input
